OL,3,CCampaigners demand compensation as
OL,4,C'our children's lives are slipping
OL,5,Caway'
OL,7,FShe continued: "This campaign is not
OL,8,Fgoing to go away. The longer they
OL,9,Fleave it the worse it is going to get.
OL,11,F"There are children living with
OL,12,Flifelong disabilities with no support
OL,13,Fand it matters.
OL,15,F"This is the government's fault. The
OL,16,Fgovernment knew at licensing that this
OL,17,Fmedicine would disable children. It is
OL,18,Fon them. The longer they leave it the
OL,19,Fmore children that are going to be
OL,20,Fborn."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/14
