OL,3,CCampaigners demand compensation as
OL,4,C'our children's lives are slipping
OL,5,Caway'
OL,7,FWhen asked about the impact of
OL,8,Fcompensation, she said it "would help
OL,9,FTyler live a more independent life,
OL,10,Fwhich is our biggest worry. He
OL,11,Fwouldn't be able to live independently
OL,12,Fbut we could put more things in place.
OL,14,F"It would be security, we wouldn't
OL,15,Fhave to worry. We'd know that he was
OL,16,Falways going to be okay when I'm not
OL,17,Fhere."
OL,19,FShe added: "It's awful and it's
OL,20,Fdisrespectful to the families. Some
OL,21,Fwomen have been fighting for so long.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/14
